description: The Republic of Ireland moves into the second phase of easing its Covid-19 lockdown measures
title: Coronavirus: Travel rules eased in Republic of Ireland and shops reopen
title_page: Coronavirus: Travel rules eased in Republic of Ireland and shops reopen - BBC News
maintext: People will be able to travel up to 20 km from their home or anywhere in their own county - up to now, the restriction was five kilometres.
